{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> δίαιτα</b> [ῐ], ἡ, <br /> <b>way of living, mode of life,</b> τὰ τῆς οἵκοι δ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 352 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; πτωχῷ δ.[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 751; σκληρὰς δ. ἐκπονεῖν 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Fragmenta” 525.5; δ. εὐτελέστεραι 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 1.3.2; δ. ἔχειν 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 490 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; δίαιταν ἔχειν ἐν Κροίσου, παρὰ τῇσι γυναιξί, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.36, 136; ξυνήθη τὴν δ. μεθ᾽ ὅπλων ποιεῖσθαι 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.6 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; δ. ποιεῖσθαι ἐν ὕδατι pass <b>one's life,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.68 (but δ. ἐποιήσατο τῶν παίδων\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] he made them <b>live,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 2.2); δ. τῆς ζόης μεταβάλλειν [prev. author] 1.157, compare 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.16 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; παρὰ τὴν δ. at <b>table,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Athenaeus Epigrammaticus 12.519b. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> δίαιτα τοῦ οὐρανοῦ· τὸ φαγεῖν, τὸ πιεῖν, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.AD(?): Hesychius Legal icographus \">Refs 5th c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>dwelling, abode,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Ethica Nicomachea” 1096a27; κοινὴ θεῶν ἁπάντων δ. “OGI” 383.27 (1st c.BC)\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; δ. πολιτικαί public <b>buildings,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.AD: Josephus Historicus “Antiquitates Judaicae” 15.9.6 \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]; <b>room</b> (or, more often, <b>suile</b> of rooms), [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ranae” 114, “CIG” “Corpus Inscriptionum Graecarum” “Corpus Inscriptionum Graecarum” 3268 (probably Smyrna), 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Publicola” 15; τὰς τῶν θεραπόντων δ. [prev. author] 2.515f \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; sailors' <b>quarters</b> in a ship, Moschion cited in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Athenaeus Epigrammaticus 5.207c \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; of fishes, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “de Mundo” 398b32. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> in Medicine texts, <b>prescribed manner of life, regimen,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ διαίτης” 1.1, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 404a, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; especially of <b>diet,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ ἀγμῶν” 36, 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus “Θρασύβουλος - Scripta Minora” 35, etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__II.2.b</b></Level4> <b>state, condition,</b> ἕλκεος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Aretaeus Medicus “περὶ αἰτιῶν καὶ σημείων χρονίων παθῶν” 2.4. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> at Athens and elsewhere, <b>arbitration,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Electra” 1073 (Lyric poetry), Legal cited in 5th-6th c.BC: Andocides Orator 1.87 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; opposed to δίκη, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Rhetorica” 1374b20; ἐμμένειν τῇ δ. 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Vespae” 524; δίαιταν ἐπιτρέψαι τινί 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 32.2, 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 18.13, 4th c.BC: Isaeus Orator 5.31 (probable reading)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ὀφλεῖν τὴν δ. to have <b>judgement</b> against one, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 29.58. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.2</b></Level3> <b>the office of arbiter,</b> δ. λαβεῖν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Hyperides Orator “pro Euxenippo” 31. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__IV</b></Level2> <b>discussion, investigation,</b> ταῦτα μακροτέρας ἐστὶ δ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC-1st c.AD: Strabo Geographus 1.1.7; δ. ποιήσασθαι περί τινος 15.1.10. (Cf.διαιτάω.) \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G6829","accentedUnicode":"δίαιτα","shortDef":"habitation","mediumDef":"habitation","stepGloss":"habitation","stepTransliteration":"diaita","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}